{"article_id":"D4STvKd8Xgtuyg2w","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"( CNN )","depth":1},{"id":1,"text":"This country is stuck with Obamacare .","depth":8},{"id":2,"text":"Republicans ca n't find the votes","depth":11},{"id":3,"text":"to repeal or replace it .","depth":11},{"id":4,"text":"Democrats ca n't agree on how to make it better .","depth":10},{"id":5,"text":"President Donald Trump just wants to move on from it .","depth":9},{"id":6,"text":"But it 's so ingrained at this point","depth":8},{"id":7,"text":"that","depth":10},{"id":8,"text":"if the courts suddenly end it ,","depth":11},{"id":9,"text":"it could completely disrupt the US health insurance system","depth":11},{"id":10,"text":"-- and not just for people","depth":11},{"id":11,"text":"who buy insurance on the exchanges","depth":12},{"id":12,"text":"created by the law .","depth":12},{"id":13,"text":"If you have health insurance","depth":12},{"id":14,"text":"or you at some point would like to have health insurance ,","depth":12},{"id":15,"text":"what happens to Obamacare will affect you .","depth":11},{"id":16,"text":"The passage the implementation and the attempted repeal of the law","depth":10},{"id":17,"text":"that remade the American health care system","depth":10},{"id":18,"text":"have each been separate dramas over the past nine years .","depth":9},{"id":19,"text":"Now begins Chapter 5 :","depth":9},{"id":20,"text":"The second court drama .","depth":9},{"id":21,"text":"The Trump administration 's about-face endorsement of a federal judge 's December decision in Texas","depth":11},{"id":22,"text":"that the Affordable Care Act is unconstitutional","depth":11},{"id":23,"text":"could create an untenable situation","depth":10},{"id":24,"text":"since , essentially , all Americans with health insurance have Obamacare now .","depth":9},{"id":25,"text":"Invalidating the entire law could strip coverage from tens of millions of Americans","depth":10},{"id":26,"text":"and strip protections for coverage","depth":11},{"id":27,"text":"enjoyed by hundreds of millions more .","depth":11},{"id":28,"text":"CNN 's Tami Luhby has documented exactly how the law touches every American","depth":10},{"id":29,"text":"-- not just the more than 20 million","depth":11},{"id":30,"text":"who have obtained Medicaid or insurance through a state or federal health insurance exchange .","depth":11},{"id":31,"text":"The fact is that exactly nine years after its passage , the Affordable Care Act ,","depth":7},{"id":32,"text":"sometimes referred to as `` Obamacare , ''","depth":7},{"id":33,"text":"has remade the US health insurance system .","depth":6},{"id":34,"text":"Despite Trump 's tweet Tuesday","depth":8},{"id":35,"text":"that the GOP will become `` the Party of Healthcare ! `` ,","depth":8},{"id":36,"text":"his pledge","depth":9},{"id":37,"text":"to take care of people with pre-existing conditions ,","depth":9},{"id":38,"text":"and his complaint Wednesday","depth":9},{"id":39,"text":"that health care coverage is too expensive ,","depth":9},{"id":40,"text":"it is increasingly , glaringly , alarmingly clear that the White House has no plan for what comes next","depth":7},{"id":41,"text":"if courts ultimately agree","depth":8},{"id":42,"text":"that the Affordable Care Act is now unconstitutional .","depth":8},{"id":43,"text":"The Republican Party will become `` The Party of Healthcare ! ''","depth":6},{"id":44,"text":"- Donald J. Trump","depth":8},{"id":45,"text":"( @ realDonaldTrump )","depth":8},{"id":46,"text":"March 26 , 2019","depth":7},{"id":47,"text":"`` The Department of Justice is part of the executive branch ,","depth":13},{"id":48,"text":"and the President has faith in his Department of Justice","depth":14},{"id":49,"text":"to do the right thing , ''","depth":14},{"id":50,"text":"senior adviser Kellyanne Conway told reporters Tuesday .","depth":12},{"id":51,"text":"`` And we 're watching litigation .","depth":13},{"id":52,"text":"We do n't predict the outcomes of litigation like that .","depth":13},{"id":53,"text":"We 'll see what happens . ''","depth":12},{"id":54,"text":"It 's a law","depth":13},{"id":55,"text":"that touches every American","depth":14},{"id":56,"text":"and gives millions of people coverage","depth":14},{"id":57,"text":"--","depth":12},{"id":58,"text":"and we 'll see what happens ?","depth":11},{"id":59,"text":"There 's a good chance","depth":11},{"id":60,"text":"the Supreme Court will ultimately weigh in , a process","depth":12},{"id":61,"text":"that could take years .","depth":12},{"id":62,"text":"But the new harder stance from Trump 's Justice Department gave the case renewed and immediate interest .","depth":10},{"id":63,"text":"`` I 'm flabbergasted , ''","depth":10},{"id":64,"text":"John Kasich said Tuesday after the court filing .","depth":10},{"id":65,"text":"He 's a Republican former Ohio governor","depth":10},{"id":66,"text":"who has emerged as a frequent Trump critic","depth":11},{"id":67,"text":"and is now a CNN contributor .","depth":11},{"id":68,"text":"As governor , he took federal money for Ohio","depth":10},{"id":69,"text":"to expand Medicaid under the law","depth":10},{"id":70,"text":"even though he has long pointed to its problems .","depth":9},{"id":71,"text":"But Kasich said","depth":10},{"id":72,"text":"the country has to address the problems ,","depth":11},{"id":73,"text":"not cut out the old law .","depth":11},{"id":74,"text":"He 's pushed a proposal","depth":11},{"id":75,"text":"hashed out with a bipartisan group of governors","depth":11},{"id":76,"text":"`` These things can all be fixed ,","depth":12},{"id":77,"text":"but you do n't need to just rip coverage away from 20 million people , ''","depth":12},{"id":78,"text":"he said .","depth":12},{"id":79,"text":"`` That 's ridiculous . ''","depth":12},{"id":80,"text":"The main trunks of the law are a massive expansion of Medicaid and a total re-creation of the individual insurance market ,","depth":8},{"id":81,"text":"but it mandated new protections in the group insurance market ,","depth":10},{"id":82,"text":"forcing insurers to cover Americans with pre-existing conditions","depth":11},{"id":83,"text":"and allowing insured people to keep covering their adult children up to age 26 .","depth":11},{"id":84,"text":"It also rewrote rules for Medicare , for hospitals and for prescription drug coverage .","depth":9},{"id":85,"text":"`` People have forgotten","depth":12},{"id":86,"text":"what it was like before the Affordable Care Act , ''","depth":12},{"id":87,"text":"said Gary Cohen , the vice president of government affairs for Blue Shield of California , one of the country 's largest insurers .","depth":11},{"id":88,"text":"Before that he worked in the Obama administration","depth":11},{"id":89,"text":"and helped implement the Affordable Care Act .","depth":11},{"id":90,"text":"`` Not only if you were sick ,","depth":13},{"id":91,"text":"but if you had ever been sick ,","depth":13},{"id":92,"text":"you were priced out ''","depth":12},{"id":93,"text":"and charged differently than other individuals ,","depth":11},{"id":94,"text":"Cohen said .","depth":10},{"id":95,"text":"To Trump 's point","depth":13},{"id":96,"text":"that health care still seems too expensive ,","depth":13},{"id":97,"text":"Cohen agreed","depth":12},{"id":98,"text":"that prices are too high ,","depth":11},{"id":99,"text":"but he argued","depth":11},{"id":100,"text":"they would be higher","depth":12},{"id":101,"text":"without the Affordable Care Act .","depth":12},{"id":102,"text":"`` I 'm sure","depth":11},{"id":103,"text":"that people are n't focused on what the trend in health care was before and after ,","depth":12},{"id":104,"text":"but there 's a lot of research","depth":13},{"id":105,"text":"that the prices have moderated , ''","depth":13},{"id":106,"text":"he said .","depth":10},{"id":107,"text":"While the administration now supports invalidating the entire law through the courts ,","depth":8},{"id":108,"text":"how the Affordable Care Act would be undone is causing experts to scratch their heads .","depth":8},{"id":109,"text":"`` The Affordable Care Act is now so woven into the rest of the health care system","depth":9},{"id":110,"text":"that trying to take it out could upset things","depth":10},{"id":111,"text":"that were not even related , ''","depth":10},{"id":112,"text":"Julie Rovner of Kaiser Health News said Tuesday on CNN .","depth":8},{"id":113,"text":"States have spent years","depth":9},{"id":114,"text":"modifying their Medicaid programs around the Affordable Care Act , for instance .","depth":9},{"id":115,"text":"That process continues","depth":9},{"id":116,"text":"as the states","depth":12},{"id":117,"text":"that have not accepted Obamacare funding","depth":13},{"id":118,"text":"to expand Medicaid with federal dollars","depth":13},{"id":119,"text":"slowly move in that direction","depth":11},{"id":120,"text":"now that the government is allowing them waivers from certain requirements","depth":11},{"id":121,"text":"or to impose new rules","depth":12},{"id":122,"text":"that people work","depth":13},{"id":123,"text":"before qualifying","depth":14},{"id":124,"text":"to receive Medicaid .","depth":14},{"id":125,"text":"`` You think about how long the bill was","depth":10},{"id":126,"text":"and how many regulations have been put in place around the law over that nine-year period .","depth":10},{"id":127,"text":"It affected every source","depth":10},{"id":128,"text":"of how people get health care , ''","depth":10},{"id":129,"text":"said Sara Collins , a vice president at the Commonwealth Fund ,","depth":10},{"id":130,"text":"which researches health care issues","depth":11},{"id":131,"text":"and pushes for improvements to the health care system .","depth":11},{"id":132,"text":"'' `` I can not overstate how disruptive this would be , ''","depth":10},{"id":133,"text":"she said .","depth":10},{"id":134,"text":"Trump 's efforts along with Republicans on Capitol Hill","depth":8},{"id":135,"text":"to repeal the law","depth":8},{"id":136,"text":"failed in 2017 ,","depth":7},{"id":137,"text":"but his administration 's attempts","depth":9},{"id":138,"text":"to chip away at it","depth":9},{"id":139,"text":"have continued ,","depth":8},{"id":140,"text":"most importantly when they used a new tax law","depth":10},{"id":141,"text":"to lower the tax","depth":12},{"id":142,"text":"assessed","depth":13},{"id":143,"text":"for not having health insurance","depth":13},{"id":144,"text":"to $ 0 .","depth":11},{"id":145,"text":"It is the lowering of the penalty","depth":11},{"id":146,"text":"that kicked off this latest drama .","depth":11},{"id":147,"text":"The judge in Texas agreed with a group of Republican state attorneys general","depth":13},{"id":148,"text":"that a $ 0 tax is n't a tax","depth":13},{"id":149,"text":"and so Chief Justice John Roberts ' tortured decision","depth":14},{"id":150,"text":"upholding the Affordable Care Act","depth":14},{"id":151,"text":"was thrown into jeopardy .","depth":13},{"id":152,"text":"That 's a turn of events worthy of a mystery novel .","depth":11},{"id":153,"text":"What will happen to Obamacare next ! ?","depth":9},{"id":154,"text":"That John Roberts ,","depth":11},{"id":155,"text":"who","depth":13},{"id":156,"text":"-- thanks to a new book by CNN 's Joan Biskupic -- we know","depth":13},{"id":157,"text":"vacillated on how to deal with the law the first time around ,","depth":12},{"id":158,"text":"might now be invested in it .","depth":10},{"id":159,"text":"Opponents of the law said","depth":9},{"id":160,"text":"the possibility","depth":11},{"id":161,"text":"of it being undone","depth":11},{"id":162,"text":"should be a wake-up call to Congress","depth":11},{"id":163,"text":"to fix it .","depth":11},{"id":164,"text":"`` The DOJ 's announcement is yet another data point","depth":10},{"id":165,"text":"that Congress needs to pass legislation","depth":11},{"id":166,"text":"that helps ,","depth":13},{"id":167,"text":"not harms ,","depth":13},{"id":168,"text":"Americans ' ability","depth":13},{"id":169,"text":"to achieve their goals of lower health care costs , better choices , and access to care","depth":14},{"id":170,"text":"when they are sick , ''","depth":14},{"id":171,"text":"said Marie Fishpaw of the conservative Heritage Foundation ,","depth":10},{"id":172,"text":"who endorses a plan","depth":11},{"id":173,"text":"that would give more power to states","depth":11},{"id":174,"text":"Democrats paid a political price","depth":13},{"id":175,"text":"for passing the Affordable Care Act ,","depth":13},{"id":176,"text":"losing control of the House of Representatives in a wave of backlash and conservative anger .","depth":12},{"id":177,"text":"Then Republicans paid a political price","depth":14},{"id":178,"text":"for coming so close to repealing it ,","depth":14},{"id":179,"text":"losing control of the House last fall ,","depth":13},{"id":180,"text":"and 41 % of voters said in exit polls","depth":13},{"id":181,"text":"that the most important issue","depth":15},{"id":182,"text":"facing the country","depth":15},{"id":183,"text":"was health care .","depth":14},{"id":184,"text":"Democrats bombarded swing districts with ads about health care and warnings about the threat","depth":13},{"id":185,"text":"of losing insurance market protections like the ban on insurance companies","depth":14},{"id":186,"text":"excluding people with pre-existing conditions .","depth":14},{"id":187,"text":"At the same time , 69 % of voters in 2016 said","depth":13},{"id":188,"text":"the health care system needs major changes .","depth":13},{"id":189,"text":"Those sentiments have given Democratic presidential candidates new energy","depth":12},{"id":190,"text":"to push the health care system further left , with new proposals for a public health insurance option or even a socialized health care system","depth":13},{"id":191,"text":"where the government takes over the insurance market .","depth":13},{"id":192,"text":"That debate was temporarily sidelined Tuesday","depth":10},{"id":193,"text":"as Democrats rallied around","depth":11},{"id":194,"text":"protecting the Affordable Care Act .","depth":11},{"id":195,"text":"More recently , American voters say by 55 % to 32 %","depth":12},{"id":196,"text":"that they 'd rather improve the current health care system","depth":13},{"id":197,"text":"than replace it ,","depth":13},{"id":198,"text":"according to a new Quinnipiac survey .","depth":11},{"id":199,"text":"Those results were published in the context of the debate","depth":13},{"id":200,"text":"pushed by Democrats","depth":13},{"id":201,"text":"about whether to move toward a single-payer health insurance system ,","depth":12},{"id":202,"text":"but they 're interesting in terms of the possibility","depth":12},{"id":203,"text":"the Trump administration could go in the other direction","depth":13},{"id":204,"text":"and have the entire Affordable Care Act invalidated .","depth":13},{"id":205,"text":"The number of Americans with favorable views of the law itself has grown","depth":12},{"id":206,"text":"and hovered around 50 % in recent years ,","depth":12},{"id":207,"text":"according to the Kaiser Family Foundation ,","depth":11},{"id":208,"text":"as the percentage of Americans with unfavorable views has fallen below 40 % .","depth":10},{"id":209,"text":"The effort","depth":11},{"id":210,"text":"to undo the law in the courts","depth":11},{"id":211,"text":"continues","depth":10},{"id":212,"text":"even as more red states find ways","depth":10},{"id":213,"text":"to expand Medicaid under it .","depth":10},{"id":214,"text":"Kasich was among the first Republican governors","depth":12},{"id":215,"text":"to buy into the almost entirely federally funded expansion of Medicaid ,","depth":12},{"id":216,"text":"and he has defended that decision ever since .","depth":11},{"id":217,"text":"But even more conservative governors are following suit ,","depth":12},{"id":218,"text":"especially now that the federal government is agreeing to special waivers from rules","depth":14},{"id":219,"text":"for accepting the money ,","depth":14},{"id":220,"text":"like requiring the insured to work .","depth":13},{"id":221,"text":"There were developments in Georgia this week , for instance ,","depth":12},{"id":222,"text":"where the GOP-controlled Legislature gave new power to the Republican governor .","depth":12},{"id":223,"text":"Fourteen states have rejected the expansion of Medicaid","depth":11},{"id":224,"text":"envisioned by the Affordable Care Act .","depth":11},{"id":225,"text":"They 're mainly in the South ,","depth":12},{"id":226,"text":"although Wisconsin is also represented .","depth":12},{"id":227,"text":"Every one of them supported Trump in 2016 .","depth":12},{"id":228,"text":"But 16 states","depth":14},{"id":229,"text":"that supported him","depth":14},{"id":230,"text":"have expanded Medicaid .","depth":13},{"id":231,"text":"In all , 4.9 million people","depth":10},{"id":232,"text":"who would otherwise be eligible for Medicaid under the Affordable Care Act","depth":10},{"id":233,"text":"are n't currently .","depth":9},{"id":234,"text":"Some of those qualify for help","depth":10},{"id":235,"text":"to buy private insurance ,","depth":10},{"id":236,"text":"but more than 2.5 million are caught in a technicality of the law :","depth":11},{"id":237,"text":"They make too much","depth":13},{"id":238,"text":"to qualify for Medicaid","depth":13},{"id":239,"text":"but not enough","depth":13},{"id":240,"text":"to qualify for help","depth":14},{"id":241,"text":"to buy private insurance .","depth":14},{"id":242,"text":"Nearly half of these in the so-called coverage gap are spread across Texas and Florida ,","depth":11},{"id":243,"text":"according to the Kaiser Family Foundation","depth":11},{"id":244,"text":"Even as red states come around","depth":5},{"id":245,"text":"and take Medicaid funds ,","depth":5},{"id":246,"text":"it does n't mean the Republicans","depth":6},{"id":247,"text":"who run those states","depth":6},{"id":248,"text":"will be supporting the law anytime soon ,","depth":5},{"id":249,"text":"but it could make it so much more difficult for so many more people","depth":4},{"id":250,"text":"if the courts suddenly take it away .","depth":4}],"relations":[{"parent":501,"left":0,"right":500,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":500,"left":493,"right":499,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":493,"left":296,"right":492,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":296,"left":283,"right":295,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":283,"left":280,"right":282,"relation":"evaluation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":280,"left":265,"right":279,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":265,"left":255,"right":264,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":255,"left":1,"right":254,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":254,"left":253,"right":5,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":253,"left":252,"right":4,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":252,"left":2,"right":3,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":264,"left":6,"right":263,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":263,"left":257,"right":262,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":257,"left":7,"right":256,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":256,"left":8,"right":9,"relation":"condition","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":262,"left":259,"right":261,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":259,"left":10,"right":258,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":258,"left":11,"right":12,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":261,"left":260,"right":15,"relation":"condition","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":260,"left":13,"right":14,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":279,"left":269,"right":278,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":269,"left":267,"right":268,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":267,"left":266,"right":18,"r